					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Thanks for this.<br /><br />I have 2 issues.<br /><br />1. I feel like arbitrary / on-the-fly X/Y splits are not a good idea. People should probably precalculate 2005/2006 values and not make the CPU do it.<br /><br />2. You are using shiru's Y scrolling system, which involves substraction (if Y scroll &gt; 240 pixels). This works fine for 2 screen high games, but you mentioned vertical scrolling. How are you going to calculate Y positions in a map that extends over 2 screens high? Division by 240?</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
