					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Probably the best way to handle maps taller than 240 pixels is to store the offset between the top of the map (in world coordinates) and the top of the 240- or 480-pixel plane explicitly, as <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=10958" class="postlink">tokumaru described</a>.</div>

